README

The program "tool2" works on both machine Linux 32 bits and Linux 64 bits.

If you have Linux 32 bits:
		1. download the folder tool_prediction_executable that contains the executable file "tool2", the jar "weka.jar", the model "model_rf_656000_linux.model",
		   and the libraries needed to run the file (libQt5Widgets.so.5, libQt5Gui.so.5, libQt5Core.so.5, libicudata.so.53, libQt5DBus.so.5, libQt5DBus.so.5.4.2,
		   libicui18n.so.53, libicuuc.so.53, platforms/libqxcb.so)
		2. decompress the file model_rf_656000_linux.model.rar
		3. On the shell, go to the path of this folder and run the command:
		   smart@imane ~/Bureau/tool_prediction_executable $ chmod u+x tool2
		   smart@imane ~/Bureau/tool_prediction_executable $ export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$(pwd):$LD_LIBRARY_PATH
		   smart@imane ~/Bureau/tool_prediction_executable/platforms $ export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$(pwd):$LD_LIBRARY_PATH
		4. Run the file tool2
		
		
	

If you have Linux 64 bits:
		1. download the folder tool_prediction_executable that contains the executable file "tool2", the jar "weka.jar", the model "model_rf_656000_linux.model",
		   and the libraries needed to run the file (libQt5Widgets.so.5, libQt5Gui.so.5, libQt5Core.so.5, libicudata.so.53, libQt5DBus.so.5, libQt5DBus.so.5.4.2,
		   libicui18n.so.53, libicuuc.so.53, platforms/libqxcb.so)
		2. decompress the file model_rf_656000_linux.model.rar
		3. Add the architecture 32 bits:
		   root@imane ~ $ sudo dpkg --add-architecture i386
		4. add the libraries needed for 32 bits:
		   root@imane ~ $ sudo apt-get install libc6:i386 libncurses5:i386 libstdc++6:i386 libgl1-mesa-glx:i386 libglib2.0-0:i386  
		5. add the libraries for 32 bits needed for xcb:
		   root@imane ~ $ sudo apt-get install libxrender1:i386 libfreetype6:i386 libfontconfig1:i386 libice6:i386 libsm6:i386 libxi6:i386
		6. check if there are any other library to install using:
		   smart@imane ~/Bureau/tool_prediction_executable $ ldd libqxcb.so
		   smart@imane ~/Bureau/tool_prediction_executable $ ldd tool2
		   (otherwise install all the libraries of 32 bits: (to avoid)) root@imane ~ $ sudo apt-get install ia32-libs
		   you can remove it later: sudo apt-get remove ia32-libs
		7. On the shell, go to the path of the folder and run the command:
		   smart@imane ~/Bureau/tool_prediction_executable $ chmod u+x tool2
		   smart@imane ~/Bureau/tool_prediction_executable $ export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$(pwd):$LD_LIBRARY_PATH
		   smart@imane ~/Bureau/tool_prediction_executable/platforms $ export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$(pwd):$LD_LIBRARY_PATH
		8. Run the file tool2
		
